data.title: Princess Helena and Prince Christian of Schleswig
data.meta_description: Carte-de-visite photograph of Princess Helena (1846-1923) and Prince Christian of Schleswig-Holstein (1831-1917), taken on their engagement: full length portrait, the Princess wearing a dress with criss-cross embroidery. Prince Christian married Helena on 5 July 1866 in the Private Chapel at Windsor Castle, As a younger son of a minor prince, he did not have any significantÂ foreign commitments and was able to live in England, so that Princess Helena could be close to her mother Queen Victoria.
